  "assistantText": "Your **Button Counter with 7-Segment Display** is fully built and ready to simulate! 🎉\n\n---\n\n## 📌 Wiring Table\n\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Pin 2** | Button (one leg) | Button input (INPUT_PULLUP) |\n| **GND** | Button (other leg) | Pulls LOW on press |\n| **Pin 3** | R_A → Segment **a** | Top bar |\n| **Pin 4** | R_B → Segment **b** | Top-right |\n| **Pin 5** | R_C → Segment **c** | Bottom-right |\n| **Pin 6** | R_D → Segment **d** | Bottom bar |\n| **Pin 7** | R_E → Segment **e** | Bottom-left |\n| **Pin 8** | R_F → Segment **f** | Top-left |\n| **Pin 9** | R_G → Segment **g** | Middle bar |\n| **GND** | Display Common Cathode | Ground for display |\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Power Budget Summary\n\n| Item | Current Draw |\n|---|---|\n| Each lit segment (5V via 220Ω) | ~18 mA |\n| Max segments ON at once (digit 8, all 7) | ~126 mA total |\n| Per Arduino I/O pin | ≤ 18 mA ✅ (under 20 mA limit) |\n| Button pull-up resistor (10 kΩ) | ~0.5 mA |\n| **Total worst-case draw** | **~127 mA** ✅ (within Uno 500 mA limit) |\n\n---\n\n## 🔢 How It Works\n\n1. **Startup** → Display shows `0`\n2. **Press button** → counter increments: `0 → 1 → 2 → ... → 9 → 0`\n3. **Debouncing** → 30 ms delay prevents false triggers from button bounce\n4. **Edge detection** → Only reacts on the falling edge (press moment), not while held",
